BY GAMI TADANYIGBE KUJE – The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) has declared Suleman Sabo of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) the winner of the February 12 Kuje Council Chairmanship Election in the Federal Capital Territory. Mr Sabo, the council’s incumbent chairman who will now serve his second term in office, defeated five other candidates in each of the 10 wards in the area council. The incumbent chairman gathered a total of 13,301 votes to defeat his closest rival, Sarki Hamidu of the All Progressives Congress (APC) who secured 7,694 votes to emerge second. Meanwhile, the Labour Party (LP) Chairmanship candidate Loveday Ajo secured 79 votes. The PDP candidate defeated the APC with a total margin of 5,607 votes. Sule Magaji, the INEC Returning Officer for the Kuje Area Council Election, announced the final results on Sunday morning. (NAN) By Gami Tadanyigbe Kuje (FCT) - The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) has declared the chairmanship candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Mr Abdulahi Sabo, winner of  the supplementary poll for Kuje Area Council, FCT. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that INEC had on March 9, declared… In "Politics" The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC), has declared the candidates of the All Progressives Congress (APC) the winners of Saturday’s chairmanship elections in three area councils of Abuja. But the commission declared the polls in Kuje and Bwari area councils inconclusive. There are six area councils in the Federal Capital… In "Politics" By Gami Tadanyigbe   Kuje     -     Mr Abdulahi Sabo has picked the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), ticket to contest for the Kuje Area Council chairmanship seat, the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN), reports. Sabo defeated four contestants to pick the ticket to chair one of the most populous area councils… In "News"